essenger of Allah, peace and blessings be upon him, would sleep lightly and then perform prayer without renewing ablution. Source: S\u0323ah\u0323i\u0304h\u0323 Muslim 376 Grade: Sahih (authentic) according to Muslim Al-Tirmidhi said, \u201cThe scholars disagreed regarding ablution for one who slept. The majority\u2026","rel":"","context":"In &quot;Wisdom \u0627\u0644\u062d\u0643\u0645\u0629&quot;","block_context":{"text":"Wisdom \u0627\u0644\u062d\u0643\u0645\u0629","link":"https:\/\/www.abuaminaelias.com\/dailyhadithonline\/category\/wisdom-al-hikmah\/"},"img":{"alt_text":"","src":"","width":0,"height":0},"classes":[]},{"id":15807,"url":"https:\/\/www.abuaminaelias.com\/dailyhadithonline\/2013\/08\/23\/wudu-friday-ghusl-better\/","url_meta":{"origin":25507,"position":2},"title":"Hadith on Ghusl: Recommendation to bathe on Friday","author":"Abu Amina Elias","date":"August 23, 2013","format":false,"excerpt":"Samurah ibn Jundab reported: The Messenger of Allah, peace and blessings be upon him, said, \u201cWhoever performs ablution on Friday has done well, but whoever performs a ritual bath has done better.\u201d Al-Shafi'i said, \"The command of the Prophet to perform a ritual bath on Friday indicates a preference for\u2026","rel":"","context":"In &quot;Righteousness \u0627\u0644\u0628\u0631&quot;","block_context":{"text":"Righteousness \u0627\u0644\u0628\u0631","link":"https:\/\/www.abuaminaelias.com\/dailyhadithonline\/category\/righteousness-al-birr\/"},"img":{"alt_text":"","src":"","width":0,"height":0},"classes":[]},{"id":15088,"url":"https:\/\/www.abuaminaelias.com\/dailyhadithonline\/2013\/07\/16\/sniff-water-nose-fasting\/","url_meta":{"origin":25507,"position":3},"title":"Hadith on Siyam: Sniff water deep in nose unless fasting","author":"Abu Amina Elias","date":"July 16, 2013","format":false,"excerpt":"Laqit ibn Sabrah reported: I said, \u201cO Messenger of Allah, tell me about ablution.\u201d The Messenger of Allah, peace and blessings be upon him, said, \